<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Degrees-of-Freedom</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Definition<keyword translate="true">Degrees-of-Freedom</keyword><keyword translate="true">DOF</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">Degrees-of-Freedom</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> of a kinematic-chain has a number of definitions. The definitions are closely related, and include:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">1: Number of independent coordinates needed to define the position of the element/mechanism...</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">- or -</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">2: The number of parameters needed to find unambiguously the geometry configuration of a system in space</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">- or -</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">3: The number of inputs needed to obtain a predictable output of a mechanism</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">- or -</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">4: The number of independent ways a kinematic-chain can move, or the number of independent coordinates or dimensions that you need to define its position.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">You can use the Gruebler Equation to calculate the number of Degrees-of-Freedom of each kinematic-chain.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The Kutzbach Criterion states that for a kinematic-chain to be useful, the number of &apos;drives&apos; (inputs) must equal the number of degree-of-freedom. In </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-size:10pt;" translate="true">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, we use a Motion-Dimensions as a &apos;Drive&apos; (input) for each degrees-of-freedom.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
